## Safety

- Never print or commit secrets, tokens, cookies, credentials, private keys, or personal data.
- Do not add logs containing request bodies, authorization headers, tokens, emails, phone numbers, or payment data.
- Destructive Git operations, bulk delete/overwrite, deployments, database migrations, and production data access require explicit human approval.

## Done Means

- Relevant tests/checks were run, or skipped checks are explained.
- Behavior changes include tests, fixtures, or manual verification notes.
- Risks and compatibility concerns are called out in the final response.
- Harness docs are updated when commands, top-level directories, APIs, or workflows change.
